title: R Packages:  The Gifts That Keep On Giving
description:
Join us on November 9th for our next R-Ladies Meetup - R Packages: The Gifts That Keep On Giving (get it? packages...gifts...this is as funny as a data scientist is going to get, ladies!)

Dr. Maria Weese will be sharing some of her favorite R packages. Molly Izenson and Sydney Harris, current MSBA students, will be sharing Data Explorer. This package is a great intro package for those of us new to R.

To receive the Zoom link for this Meetup, you will need to register here: https://miamioh.formstack.com/forms/cads_r_ladies_november_2020_meetup

title: A Journey through R
description:
We have quite a few members of this group who are excited to begin their journey in coding with R. There are others in the group who have been using R for a few years and want to advance their skills. Whatever your skill level we would like to invite you to virtually join us on October 13th to go on a Journey Through R! We will kick off this session with information on how to get started with R, along with some beginner level code lines to acclimate you to the language. We will then transition into more advanced R capabilities so you can see all that is possible in the world of R!

We are hosting this session virtually in order to keep everyone healthy and safe, and to accommodate those needing to participate remotely. Our goal is to create a network of R users so those new to R can find a more advanced mentor, as well as just develop a group any member can turn to for R advice/support.

Meeting Details:
https://miamioh.zoom.us/j/85966026510?pwd=NndMRUZaOFVUeTNzc2hUWnVWalBJZz09

We will reach out to all registered attendees with the meeting ID and passcode.

title: Understanding Your Data
description:
Join us on March 2nd, 7:00-8:00 PM ET for our first Meetup of the Spring Semester. Sydney Harris and Molly Izenson, MS Business Analytics Majors, are back to walk us through how to use R to Understand Your Data. You will learn how to use R to load in a dataset, review the different variable types, look at basic descriptive statistics (head() & str()), uncover the distribution of your data, account for missing data, etc.

To receive the Zoom link for this Meetup, you will need to register here:
https://miamioh.formstack.com/forms/cads_r_ladies_meetup_march_2021
